darrel g. mchargue (born september 26, 1954 in oklahoma city, oklahoma) is a retired american champion jockey in thoroughbred horse racing. one of five children from a family not connected to horse racing, he was first introduced to riding as a teeneage boy when he rode a neighbor's quarter horse. he was seventeen years old when he made his professional debut in 1972 at churchill downs in louisville, kentucky. the following year he was the leading rider at laurel park racecourse in laurel, maryland.